Class UnmodifiableCursor<E>

Type Parameters:
E - the type of the elements returned by this iteration.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterator<E>, Cursor<E>
public class UnmodifiableCursor<E>
extends SecureDecoratorCursor<E>

This class provides a decorator for a given iteration that cannot be modified. The methods of this class call the corresponding methods of the internally stored iteration except the methods that modify the iteration. These methods (remove and update) throws an UnsupportedOperationException.

See Also:
Iterator, Cursor, SecureDecoratorCursor
